<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                    <head>No. 96.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Foote</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23,
                            1879</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your dispatch No. 3, of the
                        26th June last, which nominates Mr. Peter A. McKellar for appointment as
                        vice-consul of the United States at Valparaiso, I have to inform you that
                        the Department deems it advisable that another nomination should be made for
                        that office. It is preferred that an American citizen be named if
                        practicable.</p>
                    <p>Your dispatch No. 8, of August 22 last, has been received.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Second Assistant
                                Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
            </body></text></TEI>